  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Add Ball-Joint</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Ball-Joint</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text">You must do <text styleclass="T_Menu">Add Ball-Joint</text>&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName-IT" style="font-style:normal; color:#ff0000;">two</text><text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">(2)</text> times, to add a <text styleclass="Element">Ball-Joint</text> to each end of one <text styleclass="Element">Part</text>. The <text styleclass="Element">Part</text> with a <text styleclass="Element">Ball-Joint</text> at each end has the derived name of <text styleclass="Interface">Connecting-Part</text>.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text">One <text styleclass="Element">Ball-Joint</text> joins the <text styleclass="Interface">Connecting-Part</text> to a <text styleclass="Element">Part</text> in the active <text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Editor</text>. </para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text">The other <text styleclass="Element">Ball-Joint</text> joins the <text styleclass="Interface">connecting Part</text> to a <text styleclass="Element">Part</text> in a different <text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Editor.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="3" style="width:auto;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:120px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="MD-BallJoints-ConnectingPart.ipp" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"><title>Pin-Joints in MechDesigner</title><caption><![CDATA[2x Ball-Joints in MechDesigner]]></caption></image></para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:180px;">
          <para styleclass="Image Caption"><image src="MD-BallJoints-Real.ipp" imagestyleclass="Default" scale="-99.90%" figurelistinclude="0"><caption><![CDATA[Rod-End Bearing]]></caption></image></para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:141px;">
          <para styleclass="Image Caption"><image src="MD-BsllJointSW.png" imagestyleclass="Default" scale="-99.90%" figurelistinclude="0"><caption><![CDATA[2 x Ball-Joint in
SOLIDWORKS]]></caption></image></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="VariableName">Terminology: </para>
    <para styleclass="Body Table"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="7" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:153px;">
          <para styleclass="Element" style="text-align:right;">Ball-Joint :<text styleclass="Popup Box2">&#32;</text></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">A <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Ball-Joint</text> makes a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Point</text> in a <text styleclass="Popup Box2">Connecting-Part</text> to be coincident with a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Point</text> in a different <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Part</text>.</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">You must add 2 x <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Ball-Joints</text> - 1 x <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Ball-Joint</text> to each end of a <text styleclass="Popup Box2">Connecting-Part:</text></para>
          <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Popup Box" style="margin-left:15px; font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Popup Box" style="margin-left:15px;">1 x <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Ball-Joint </text>is between a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Point</text> in the <text styleclass="Popup Box2">Connecting-Part</text> and a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Part</text> in the active Mechanism-Editor</li>
          </list>
          <list id="1" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Popup Box" style="margin-left:15px; font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Popup Box" style="margin-left:15px;">1 x <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Ball-Joint </text>is between a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Point</text> in the <text styleclass="Popup Box2">Connecting-Part</text> and a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Part</text> in the different Mechanism-Editor</li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:153px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box" style="text-align:right;">&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName-small">Spherical-Joint: </text></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">The kinematic and equivalent term for a <text styleclass="Element">Ball-Joint.</text>&#32;</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:153px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box2" style="text-align:right;">Kinematics-Tree : </para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">Joints in a <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Dyad</text> use the letter <text styleclass="VariableName-small">S</text> for a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Ball-Joint</text>.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td colspan="2">
          <para styleclass="VariableName-small">Derived Names: </para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:153px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box2" style="text-align:right;">Connecting Part : </para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">A <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Part</text> with a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Ball-Joint</text> at its <text styleclass="Popup Box2">start-Point</text> and at its <text styleclass="Popup Box2">end-Point</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:153px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box2" style="text-align:right;">Completely-Free Part :</para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">A <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Part</text> with 3 degrees-of-freedom</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:153px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box2" style="text-align:right;">Free Part : </para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">A <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Part</text> with 1 or 2 degrees-of-freedom </para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="SeeAlso">See also:<text styleclass="Body Text">&#32;</text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Dialog-BallJoint">Ball-Joint dialog-box</link>, <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="" anchor="EditConnecting-Part">Connecting Part Length and Diameter</link>.</para>
    <para styleclass="SeeAlso">See also <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-POP-Ball-Joint-Configurations">Ball-Joint configurations</link></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
